<package >
  <metadata>
    <id>CocktailCTP</id>
    <version>0.3.0</version>
    <authors>Marcel Good, Ward Bell, Rob Eisenberg</authors>
    <owners>IdeaBlade</owners>
    <licenseUrl>http://cocktail.ideablade.com/licensing</licenseUrl>
    <projectUrl>http://cocktail.ideablade.com/</projectUrl>
    <requireLicenseAcceptance>true</requireLicenseAcceptance>
    <summary>Cocktail is an application development platform that takes the pain out of the development of data-driven Rich Internet Applications (RIA) in Silverlight or WPF Desktop Applications.</summary>
    <description>Cocktail leverages established patterns and approaches, such as MVVM und builds on DevForce 2010 rich data service capabilities.</description>
    <releaseNotes>
      - New: Generic OperationResult&lt;T&gt; class for returning result values from asynchronous operations.
      - New: Additional AsOperationResult extension methods for the various DevForce operations.
      - Breaking change: Enhanced DialogManager to support a default button, enter and ESC keys (Method signature change).
      - New: Improved look and feel of DialogManager for WPF.
      - Fix: Threading issue during asynchronous bootstrapping in WPF.
      - Fix: Duplicate log output if DevForces fails to create log file.
      - New: Seperate solutions to build Cocktail for WPF, Silerlight 4 and Silverlight 5 only.
      - New: WPF version of TempHire
      - Enhancements to TempHire.
      - Minor code cleanup and optimizations.
    </releaseNotes>
    <copyright>Copyright 2012</copyright>
    <tags>Cocktail,DevForce,Silverlight,WPF</tags>
  </metadata>
